In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June 2012 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. He highlights the significance of music as a part of American culture, bringing people together and expressing shared humanity. The president acknowledges the contributions of African-American musicians throughout history, from spiritual hymns during slavery to jazz, blues, and contemporary genres. He emphasizes the resilience and creativity of African-American musicians, and encourages public officials, educators, and the general public to observe this month with activities and programs that promote awareness and appreciation of music composed, arranged, or performed by African Americans.